<script>
  import { Box, Stack, Text, Truncate } from "carbon-components-svelte";
</script>

Text applies Carbon typography to any element: type scale, semantic color, and layout modifiers. It covers productive styles for application UI and expressive styles for editorial layouts.

## Default

The default component renders a `<p>` with the `body-long-01` type style.

<Text>Carbon Components Svelte implements the Carbon Design System.</Text>

## Text color

Set `color` to a Carbon semantic text token. Each token describes intent and resolves to the active theme, so colors update when the theme changes.

| Token         | Description                                                   |
| ------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `primary`     | Primary text for headings and body copy                       |
| `secondary`   | Secondary text for supplementary copy                         |
| `placeholder` | Placeholder text in form inputs                               |
| `helper`      | Helper and caption text                                       |
| `on-color`    | Text on a colored background, such as a button or tag         |
| `inverse`     | Text on an inverse surface, such as a tooltip or notification |
| `error`       | Error and validation text                                     |
| `disabled`    | Disabled text                                                 |

<Text color="primary">Primary text</Text>
<Text color="secondary">Secondary text</Text>
<Text color="placeholder">Placeholder text</Text>
<Text color="helper">Helper text</Text>
<Text color="error">Error text</Text>
<Text color="disabled">Disabled text</Text>

`on-color` and `inverse` are meant for colored or inverse surfaces, where the default text tokens would be unreadable. Both read light in the white theme but track different surfaces, so they diverge in other themes. Each example places the token on the surface it is designed for.

Use `on-color` for text on a colored background, such as a button or tag fill. [Box](/components/Box) has no fill token for interactive surfaces, so set the background on the container:

<Box padding={5} style="background-color: var(--cds-interactive-01)">
  <Text color="on-color">Text on a colored background</Text>
</Box>

Use `inverse` for text on an inverse surface, such as a tooltip or notification:

<Box fill="inverse" padding={5}>
  <Text color="inverse">Text on an inverse surface</Text>
</Box>

## Type styles

Set `type` to a Carbon type token. The scale covers supporting text, body copy, and the productive and expressive heading sets. Productive styles use fixed sizes for dense product UI; expressive styles scale fluidly with the viewport for editorial layouts.

| Token                     | Description                                              |
| ------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------- |
| `caption-01`              | Smallest supporting text for captions and footnotes      |
| `caption-02`              | Caption text, one step larger                            |
| `label-01`                | Form field and UI labels                                 |
| `label-02`                | Label text, one step larger                              |
| `helper-text-01`          | Helper text beneath form inputs                          |
| `helper-text-02`          | Helper text, one step larger                             |
| `body-short-01`           | Dense, single-line body text                             |
| `body-short-02`           | Dense body text, one step larger                         |
| `body-long-01`            | Paragraph body text for multiple lines                   |
| `body-long-02`            | Paragraph body text, one step larger                     |
| `code-01`                 | Inline code set in IBM Plex Mono                         |
| `code-02`                 | Code text, one step larger                               |
| `heading-01`              | Bold heading for dense UI                                |
| `heading-02`              | Bold heading, one step larger                            |
| `productive-heading-01`   | Productive heading scale, step 1 (smallest)              |
| `productive-heading-02`   | Productive heading scale, step 2                         |
| `productive-heading-03`   | Productive heading scale, step 3                         |
| `productive-heading-04`   | Productive heading scale, step 4                         |
| `productive-heading-05`   | Productive heading scale, step 5                         |
| `productive-heading-06`   | Productive heading scale, step 6 (light weight)          |
| `productive-heading-07`   | Productive heading scale, step 7 (largest, light weight) |
| `expressive-paragraph-01` | Fluid paragraph for editorial layouts                    |
| `expressive-heading-01`   | Expressive heading, step 1                               |
| `expressive-heading-02`   | Expressive heading, step 2                               |
| `expressive-heading-03`   | Expressive heading, fluid above step 2                   |
| `expressive-heading-04`   | Expressive heading, fluid                                |
| `expressive-heading-05`   | Expressive heading, fluid                                |
| `expressive-heading-06`   | Expressive heading, fluid (largest)                      |
| `quotation-01`            | Fluid quotation set in IBM Plex Serif                    |
| `quotation-02`            | Quotation, one step larger                               |
| `display-01`              | Largest fluid display text                               |
| `display-02`              | Display text, fluid                                      |
| `display-03`              | Display text, fluid                                      |
| `display-04`              | Display text, fluid (largest)                            |

