## Custom element

Set `tag` to render a different element. Type and color apply to whichever tag you choose.

<Text tag="em" type="body-short-01">Inline emphasis</Text>
<Text tag="blockquote" type="quotation-01">A quotation rendered as a blockquote.</Text>

## Modifiers

Set modifier props alongside a type style.

<Stack gap={5}>
  <Text type="body-long-01" weight="light">Light weight (300)</Text>
  <Text type="body-long-01" weight="regular">Regular weight (400)</Text>
  <Text type="body-long-01" weight="semibold">Semibold weight (600)</Text>
  <Text type="body-long-01" italic>Italic body text</Text>
  <Text type="body-long-01" family="mono">IBM Plex Mono</Text>
  <Text type="body-long-01" family="serif">IBM Plex Serif</Text>
  <Text tag="h2" type="productive-heading-04" balance maxWidth="20rem">Balanced heading across multiple lines</Text>
</Stack>

Set `wrap` to `break-word` to break long words, or `nowrap` to keep text on one line.

<Box maxWidth="12rem" border="subtle" padding={3}>
  <Text type="body-short-01" wrap="break-word">supercalifragilisticexpialidocious@example.com</Text>
</Box>

<Box maxWidth="12rem" border="subtle" padding={3}>
  <Text type="body-short-01" wrap="nowrap">This line will not wrap to the next row.</Text>
</Box>

### Max width and full width

Set `maxWidth` to any CSS length. Numbers are treated as pixels; strings accept units such as `ch`, `rem`, `%`, or `px`. Text fills its container by default. Neither `maxWidth` nor `fullWidth` is applied unless you set them.

<Stack gap={5}>
  <Text type="body-long-01" maxWidth="38ch">
    Character measure (`38ch`) scales with the font size and is useful for readable line length.
  </Text>
  <Text type="body-long-01" maxWidth="20rem">
    Rem-based width (`20rem`) tracks the root font size.
  </Text>
  <Text type="body-long-01" maxWidth={480}>
    Pixel width (`480`) when you need a fixed cap.
  </Text>
</Stack>

`fullWidth` sets `width: 100%`. A block element already spans its parent; use `fullWidth` in flex or grid layouts where width must be explicit. Pair it with `maxWidth` when the row is full width but the copy should stay capped. Use [Box](/components/Box) for the bordered container:

<Box border="subtle" padding={5} fullWidth>
  <Text type="body-long-01" fullWidth maxWidth="38ch">
    This paragraph fills the container row but stops at 38ch.
  </Text>
</Box>

<Box border="subtle" padding={5} fullWidth>
  <Text type="body-long-01" fullWidth>
    Without `maxWidth`, `fullWidth` stretches across the entire container.
  </Text>
</Box>

## Truncate (multiline)

Set `lines` to truncate overflow while keeping a Carbon type style applied. Values above `1` use multiline mode (end clamp only). See also [Truncate](/components/Truncate) and the `truncate` action for use on native elements.

<Text type="body-long-01" maxWidth="20rem" lines={3}>
  Carbon Components Svelte is a Svelte component library that implements the Carbon Design System, an open source design system by IBM. It is maintained by the open source community and is available on npm.
</Text>

Alternatively, wrap an inline `Text` element with the `Truncate` component:

<Truncate lines={3}>
  <Box maxWidth="20rem">
    <Text tag="span" type="body-long-02">
      Carbon Components Svelte is a Svelte component library that implements the Carbon Design System, an open source design system by IBM. It is maintained by the open source community and is available on npm.
    </Text>
  </Box>
</Truncate>

## Typography inspiration

Combine `type`, `color`, and `tag` as you would on an IBM product page: expressive type for editorial moments, productive type for application UI.

<Stack gap={8}>
  <Text type="caption-02" color="secondary">IBM Cloud · Observability</Text>
  <Text tag="h1" type="display-03" color="primary">See what your systems are telling you</Text>
  <Text type="expressive-paragraph-01" color="primary" maxWidth="44ch">Before an incident reaches your customers, traces and logs already carry the signal. IBM Cloud Observability brings metrics, logs, and traces into one workspace so your team can investigate faster and ship with confidence.</Text>
  <Stack gap={5}>
    <Text tag="h2" type="productive-heading-05" color="primary">Unified telemetry across hybrid cloud</Text>
    <Text type="body-long-02" color="primary" maxWidth="52ch">Connect Kubernetes clusters on Red Hat OpenShift, virtual servers, and managed services without reconfiguring your instrumentation. Retention policies and access controls follow the governance model your organization already uses in IBM Cloud.</Text>
  </Stack>
  <Text tag="blockquote" type="quotation-01" color="primary" maxWidth="24ch">Good typography earns trust by staying out of the way while you make decisions that matter.</Text>
  <Stack gap={2}>
    <Text tag="h4" type="heading-02" color="primary">Active incidents</Text>
    <Text type="body-short-01" color="secondary">3 open · Last updated 2 minutes ago</Text>
    <Text type="caption-01" color="placeholder">Metrics retained for 30 days on the Standard plan.</Text>
  </Stack>
  <Box fill="layer-01" padding={6} border="subtle" maxWidth="42rem">
    <Stack gap={6}>
      <Text tag="h3" type="productive-heading-03" color="primary">Create an ingestion endpoint</Text>
      <Text type="body-long-01" color="secondary" maxWidth="42ch">API keys authenticate programmatic access to your observability workspace. Store secrets in IBM Cloud Secrets Manager and rotate them on a schedule your security team defines.</Text>
      <Stack gap={1}>
        <Text type="label-01" color="primary">Service name</Text>
        <Text type="helper-text-01" color="helper">Use lowercase letters, numbers, and hyphens.</Text>
      </Stack>
    </Stack>
  </Box>
</Stack>

## Utility classes

Apply Carbon type utilities directly when you do not need the component. Classes use the `bx--` prefix.

| Class | Description |
| ----- | ----------- |
| `bx--type-{token}` | Carbon type style. See [Type styles](#type-styles) for tokens |
| `bx--type-text-primary` | Primary text color |
| `bx--type-text-secondary` | Secondary text color |
| `bx--type-text-placeholder` | Placeholder text color |
| `bx--type-text-helper` | Helper text color |
| `bx--type-text-on-color` | Text on a colored background |
| `bx--type-text-inverse` | Text on an inverse surface |
| `bx--type-text-error` | Error text color |
| `bx--type-text-disabled` | Disabled text color |
| `bx--type-mono` | IBM Plex Mono |
| `bx--type-sans` | IBM Plex Sans |
| `bx--type-sans-condensed` | IBM Plex Sans Condensed |
| `bx--type-sans-hebrew` | IBM Plex Sans Hebrew |
| `bx--type-serif` | IBM Plex Serif |
| `bx--type-light` | Font weight 300 |
| `bx--type-regular` | Font weight 400 |
| `bx--type-semibold` | Font weight 600 |
| `bx--type-italic` | Italic |
| `bx--type-break-word` | Break long words |
| `bx--type-nowrap` | Keep text on one line |
| `bx--type-balance` | Balance line lengths |
| `bx--type-full-width` | Span the full container width (`width: 100%`) |

<p class="bx--type-heading-02">Styled with bx--type-heading-02</p>
<p class="bx--type-body-long-01 bx--type-semibold">Semibold body text</p>
<p class="bx--type-body-long-01" style="max-width: 38ch">Constrained with inline max-width</p>
